### Initialize Sentry SDK in AppDelegate

Source: https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-docs/blob/master/docs/platforms/apple/guides/ios/manual-setup.mdx

Configure and start the Sentry SDK within your application's AppDelegate. This ensures the SDK is initialized early in the application lifecycle. Key options include DSN, debug mode, and traces sample rate.

```swift
import Sentry // Make sure you import Sentry

// ....

func application(_ application: UIApplication,
    didFinishLaunchingWithOptions launchOptions: [UIApplication.LaunchOptionsKey: Any]?) -> Bool {

    SentrySDK.start { options in
        options.dsn = "___PUBLIC_DSN___"
        options.debug = true // Enabled debug when first installing is always helpful

        // Set tracesSampleRate to 1.0 to capture 100% of transactions for performance monitoring.
        // We recommend adjusting this value in production.
        options.tracesSampleRate = 1.0
    }

    return true
}
```

```objectivec
@import Sentry;

- (BOOL)application:(UIApplication *)application didFinishLaunchingWithOptions:(NSDictionary *)launchOptions {

    [SentrySDK startWithConfigureOptions:^(SentryOptions *options) {
        options.dsn = @"___PUBLIC_DSN___";
        options.debug = YES; // Enabled debug when first installing is always helpful

        // Set tracesSampleRate to 1.0 to capture 100% of transactions for performance monitoring.
        // We recommend adjusting this value in production.
        options.tracesSampleRate = @1.0;
    }];

    return YES;
}
```

--------------------------------

### Initialize Sentry SDK in AppDelegate (Swift)

Source: https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-docs/blob/master/platform-includes/getting-started-config/apple.mdx

Initializes the Sentry SDK within the AppDelegate's `application:didFinishLaunchingWithOptions` method. This is the recommended approach for traditional iOS apps. It requires importing the Sentry SDK and configuring the DSN and other options.

```swift
import Sentry // Make sure you import Sentry

// ....

func application(_ application: UIApplication,
    didFinishLaunchingWithOptions launchOptions: [UIApplication.LaunchOptionsKey: Any]?) -> Bool {

    SentrySDK.start { options in
        options.dsn = "___PUBLIC_DSN___"
        options.debug = true // Enabled debug when first installing is always helpful

        // Set tracesSampleRate to 1.0 to capture 100% of transactions for performance monitoring.
        // We recommend adjusting this value in production.
        options.tracesSampleRate = 1.0
    }

    return true
}
```

--------------------------------

### Initialize Sentry SDK in Swift

Source: https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-docs/blob/master/platform-includes/configuration/config-intro/apple.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to initialize the Sentry SDK in a Swift application. It requires importing the Sentry framework and calling the `start` method with your DSN. Debug mode is enabled for easier troubleshooting during initial setup.

```swift
import Sentry // Make sure you import Sentry

// ....

func application(_ application: UIApplication,
    didFinishLaunchingWithOptions launchOptions: [UIApplication.LaunchOptionsKey: Any]?) -> Bool {

    SentrySDK.start { options in
        options.dsn = "___PUBLIC_DSN___"
        options.debug = true // Enabled debug when first installing is always helpful
    }

    return true
}
```

--------------------------------

### Initialize Sentry SDK on Apple Platforms

Source: https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-docs/blob/master/includes/apple-platform-getting-started.mdx

Initializes the Sentry SDK within the application lifecycle to capture errors and performance data. Supports configuration for DSN, PII collection, profiling, session replay, and experimental logging features.

```swift
import Sentry

func application(_ application: UIApplication,
    didFinishLaunchingWithOptions launchOptions: [UIApplication.LaunchOptionsKey: Any]?) -> Bool {

    SentrySDK.start { options in
        options.dsn = "___PUBLIC_DSN___"
        options.debug = true
        options.sendDefaultPii = true
        options.tracesSampleRate = 1
        options.configureProfiling = {
            $0.lifecycle = .trace
            $0.sessionSampleRate = 1
        }
        options.sessionReplay.onErrorSampleRate = 1.0
        options.sessionReplay.sessionSampleRate = 0.1
        options.experimental.enableLogs = true
    }

    return true
}
```

```objective-c
@import Sentry;

- (BOOL)application:(UIApplication *)application didFinishLaunchingWithOptions:(NSDictionary *)launchOptions {

    [SentrySDK startWithConfigureOptions:^(SentryOptions *options) {
        options.dsn = @"___PUBLIC_DSN___";
        options.debug = YES;
        options.sendDefaultPii = YES;
        options.tracesSampleRate = @1.f;
        options.configureProfiling = ^(SentryProfileOptions *profiling) {
            profiling.lifecycle = SentryProfileLifecycleTrace;
            profiling.sessionSampleRate = 1.f;
        };
        options.sessionReplay.onErrorSampleRate = 1.0;
        options.sessionReplay.sessionSampleRate = 0.1;
        options.experimental.enableLogs = YES;
    }];

    return YES;
}
```

```swift
import Sentry

@main
struct SwiftUIApp: App {
    init() {
        SentrySDK.start { options in
            options.dsn = "___PUBLIC_DSN___"
            options.debug = true
            options.sendDefaultPii = true
            options.tracesSampleRate = 1
            options.configureProfiling = {
                $0.lifecycle = .trace
                $0.sessionSampleRate = 1
            }
            options.sessionReplay.onErrorSampleRate = 1.0
            options.sessionReplay.sessionSampleRate = 0.1
            options.experimental.enableLogs = true
        }
    }
}
```

### Manual Setup > Configuration

Source: https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-docs/blob/master/docs/platforms/apple/guides/ios/manual-setup.mdx

We recommend initializing the SDK on the main thread as soon as possible – in your AppDelegate `application:didFinishLaunchingWithOptions` method, for example. This ensures that the SDK is ready to capture events from the earliest moments of your application's lifecycle. You need to import Sentry and provide your DSN. Enabling debug mode is helpful during initial setup. For performance monitoring, set `tracesSampleRate` to 1.0 to capture all transactions; adjust this in production.

